{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"alias":"rife-serif-fist","description":"# gitleaks false-positive on a docs example secret blocks docs changes (+ 189 unblock)\n\n## What\ngitleaks' generic-api-key rule flags a DOCUMENTED throwaway placeholder in docs\n(docs/llm-framework.md:311 `export LANGFUSE_SECRET_KEY=sk-lf-1234567890`), and because the\nsecret detector scans the whole CHANGED FILE, any edit to that file (e.g. change 189) is\nforce-BLOCKed. Fix the false-positive class without weakening detection of genuine secrets.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Add a `.gitleaks.toml` allowlist scoped to documented placeholder patterns (sk-lf-/pk-lf- throwaways; docs example keys) — NOT a blanket **/*.md exclusion (a real doc secret must still block).\n- [ ] Fix the misleading docs/llm-framework.md:311 placeholder to an obviously-non-secret form.\n- [ ] The secret detector still fail-closes on a genuine secret (a test/fixture proves a real pattern still matches).\n- [ ] This sits at/before change 189 in the Gerrit stack so 189's re-review passes gitleaks; make lint green; commit carries a rebar-ticket trailer.","id":"a6a5-f4a0-c5e6-40a8","parent_id":"9322-f84a-e047-4471","priority":1,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"gitleaks false-positive on docs example secret blocks docs changes"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783060805822400001,"uuid":"8e19648b-7207-4508-82f3-24287b47f68f"}